{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17506697","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17506697"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:45:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:45:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2559"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2559"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.01,0.22,0.36,0.26]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2559"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37772"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2559","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2559"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2021-05-04T23:49:57+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-29T23:27:36+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2024-08-29T23:27:36+09:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-27 11:03:32"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2559"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"16151"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"831"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22330"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2627"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2647"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14811"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22330"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37772","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/37772"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 90-year-old is brought to the clinic by her daughter following a fall at home. The fall was unwitnessed and the patient describes tripping on the edge of a rug. She describes some dizziness preceding the fall, but states this is relatively common. She did not lose consciousness, and had no chest pain or shortness breath. She reports no head strike, weakness or sensory changes, and was not confused afterwards or incontinent of urine.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHer past medical history includes urinary incontinence, degenerative facet joint hypertrophy, type 2 diabetes mellitus and hay fever. Her regular medications are oxybutynin, amitriptyline, metformin and promethazine.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EExamination is unremarkable except for a pulse of 120/min.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her fall?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mechanical fall","Ischaemic event","Polypharmacy","Anticholinergic burden","Postural hypotension"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA good approach to \u003Cstrong\u003Efalls\u003C/strong\u003E assessment is needed. Consideration of events pre-fall, during the fall and after the fall is essential. In this patient there is no clinical evidence of an acute cardiac or neurological event (e.g. stroke, seizure), so \u003Cstrong\u003Eischaemic event\u003C/strong\u003E is unlikely. There is also no clear history of postural dizziness that would suggest \u003Cstrong\u003Epostural hypotension\u003C/strong\u003E as the cause.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient is on a number of medications. Significantly, she is on oxybutynin, amitriptyline and promethazine, all of which have anticholinergic effects. In the elderly, there is a high sensitivity to the \u003Cstrong\u003Eanticholinergic burden\u003C/strong\u003E from medications and one manifestation of this is dizziness leading to falls. These medications ideally should be avoided or reduced in the geriatric population. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolypharmacy\u003C/strong\u003E is defined as a patient being on \u0026gt;5 medications. Whilst this patient is only on 4 medications, the specific combination is impacting her risk of falls.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this patient the anticholinergic burden is the cause of her falls, so a \u003Cstrong\u003Emechanical fall\u003C/strong\u003E is not the correct diagnosis. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Polypharmacy is defined as a patient being on \u003E5 medications.","In the elderly, there is a high sensitivity to the anticholinergic burden from medications"],"references":["Bell JS, Mezrani C, Blacker N, LeBlanc T, Frank O, Alderman CP, Rossi S, Rowett, Shute R. Anticholinergic and sedative medicines Prescribing considerations for people with dementia. AFP. 2012; 41 (1): 45-49."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22330"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2559"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/22330"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-07-06T14:22:14+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-08-29T23:28:20+09:30","number":6,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2024-08-29T23:27:31+09:30","plagiarismScore":0,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-2559-6.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250929%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250929T021544Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=2a57970daebeda058c993156d7bf1b996752fd99343fb2860a91ad565ce075b0"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2559"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37772"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"use